briefdescription.para: Get the value of an existing dictionary entry and check that it is in a specified range.

detaileddescription.para: The range is specified by two parameters min and max which have the same type as the template argument. The last parameter mode defines the type of the range:

sect2.title: Mode Relation
sect2.para: 0 min < x < max 1 min <= x < max 2 min <= x <= max

parameterdescription.para: An entry of the given name is not known in the dictionary.
if a value is outside the range

briefdescription.para: Provide a value to a property DoubleVectorDatum in the dictionary.

detaileddescription.para: In contrast to append_property, this function adds the value only once to the property. On all subsequent events, it ensures that the value passed in is identical to the value present. This is needed by recording_decive.

briefdescription.para: Provide a value to a property IntVectorDatum in the dictionary.

briefdescription.para: Add values of a vector<double> to a property DoubleVectorDatum in the dictionary.

detaileddescription.para: This variant of append_property is for adding vector<double>s to vector<double>s of the same size. It is required for collecting data across threads when multimeter is running in accumulation mode.
